com.alexgilleran.icesoap.xpath

Class XPathRepository<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.alexgilleran.icesoap.xpath.XPathRepository<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The object to store against xpaths - used for Field by parsers, but can be anything.

    public class XPathRepository<T>
extends Object
    Akin to a map that stores objects against an XPath value. Lookup logic is according to XPath matching - i.e. if a object is stored in the repository against the xpath /this/is/an/xpath and get is executed with the XPathElement //xpath, the stored object will be returned. This is achieved via simple mapping against XPathElement.getName(), then confirmation via XPathElement.matches(XPathElement). This means that retrieval of objects from the repository is fastest using smaller numbers of shorter xpaths with different names. Retrieval when the repository is filled with a large number of xpaths with the same names but different predicates will slow retrieval down.
    Author:
    Alex Gilleran

      • remove

        public T remove(XPathElement key)
        Removes the record with the supplied key from the repository. Note that this does not attempt to match the XPathElement passed in - the key supplied to remove(XPathElement) must exactly equal the one in the repository.
        Parameters:
        key - The (exact) key of the record to remove.
        Returns:
        The value of the removed record. null will be returned if no value is found, or if null was stored against the supplied key.
